dataset.description:
Summary
Centerline data was developed for cartographic and geocoding purposes.  The attributes of the centerline data are in the MetroGIS Standard format.

Description
The geometry of the centerline data is created and maintained by the Carver County's Survey Department.  The attribution of the centerline data is a collaborative effort between the Survey Office and GIS Office.
dataset.title: Centerlines

dataset.description:
Summary
Parcel data was developed to map and track property boundaries. The attributes of the parcel data are in the MetroGIS Standard format.

Description

The geometry of parcels were created by Carver County's Survey department using COGO in an AutoCad environment. The AutoCad lines have been imported into a ArcGIS Geodatabase and polygons built. These polygons are attributed with a Parcel Identification Number (PID). The GIS polygons are joined by PID to the Assessor's CAMA system and Taxpayer Services tax database to show attributes of the property.
dataset.title: Parcels

dataset.description:
Summary Carver County address point dataset.
Description

Address points are maintained by different addressing authorities within Carver County. The dataset is based upon the MetroGIS Address Points Standards, derived from the National Address Standard. This dataset contains situs addresses, they are not used for contact of individuals, but instead for the relating of features to a specific location.
dataset.title: AddressPoints

dataset.description:
Summary
The 10 ft contours provide a high level of detail for cartographic representations of the topography within Carver County.  The county utilizes the 10 ft contours for purposes of land records management, infrastructure management, engineering pre-design, map production and various land data analysis.

Description
Fugro Horizons Inc. acquired highly accurate Light Detection and Ranging (LiDAR) elevation data for the Twin Cities metropolitan region in east-central Minnesota in Spring and Fall 2011, with some reflights in Spring 2012. 1.5 points/square meter covers the Carver County Data.
A DEM was created from a terrain using bare-earth multipoint PointZ and hydro-breaklines. The Terrain was then converted to a Raster DEM using a 1-meter cell-size.
Two-foot contours were created by resampling the 1-meter DEM to 3 meters, then smoothing the 3-meter grid using a neighborhood average routine, and then creating contours from this surface using standard ArcGIS processing tools.
Ten-foot contours were created from the two-foot contour features.
dataset.title: 10 Ft Contours
